**Turn 1**  
- Swamp -> ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) -> [Dark Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=54) -> ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol);  
- with ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) [Entomb](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=30552) Emrakul; Emrakul's triggered ability which forces you to shuffle your graveyard into your library triggers and goes on the stack;  
- with ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) cast [Shallow Grave](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=3310); It goes on top of the stack, above the triggered ability;  
- Shallow Grave resolves, and Emrakul enters the battlefield with haste;  
- Emrakul's triggered ability resolves, and you shuffle your (empty) graveyard into your library;  
- **ATTACK!!!**

[Door to nothingness](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Door to nothingness) costs ![5](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=5&type=symbol)![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol)![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol)![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) to one shot someone. This can do it for ![15](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=15&type=symbol) and cant be countered. Why does door come into play tapped again?  

@SteamyRayvon  
Notice the keyword "Cast". You actually have to pay its mana cost, normally from your hand as well, to cast this card. You can very well cheat this into play with [Quicksilver Amulet](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Quicksilver Amulet) or [Elvish Piper](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Elvish Piper), but you don't get an extra turn from it.   

@Greenman  
[Oblivion Ring](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Oblivion Ring), and [Journey to Nowhere](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Journey to Nowhere) still very much work against Emrakul. When they hit the battlefield they are not spells, they are permanents with triggered abilities going on the stack. Emrakul does not have protection from abilities. I bring this up because I couldn't tell you how many [polymorph](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=polymorph) decks I played in zendikar standard that got hosed by my oblivion ring. Hes not as sturdy as he looks!

@knight3607  

As [Phyrexian Ingester](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phyrexian Ingester) enters the battlefield, it is a permanent and no longer a spell. Emrakul will not have protection from it.  

@SteamyRayvon6969: You don't get the extra turn with a [quicksilver amulet](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=quicksilver amulet) (or with [show and tell](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=show and tell), [elvish piper](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=elvish piper), [aether vial](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=aether vial) etc). It specifically says when you CAST it. You CAST it with either of the following:  
\* 15 mana  
\* [Omniscience](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Omniscience)
